      "date": "2019-09-03 21:20:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nLooking at the suite_log for one of these test sessions, https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/f0703700-cb6f-11e9-9fc9-52540065bddc , I see some errors related to identity_upcall. For example in test 25, I see\n\nCMD: trevis-67vm4,trevis-67vm5 /usr/sbin/lctl set_param mdt.*.identity_upcall=NONE\ntrevis-67vm4: error: set_param: setting /sys/fs/lustre/mdt/lustre-MDT0000/identity_upcall=NONE: wrote only 1\ntrevis-67vm4: error: set_param: setting /sys/fs/lustre/mdt/lustre-MDT0002/identity_upcall=NONE: wrote only 1\ntrevis-67vm5: error: set_param: setting /sys/fs/lustre/mdt/lustre-MDT0001/identity_upcall=NONE: wrote only 1\ntrevis-67vm5: error: set_param: setting /sys/fs/lustre/mdt/lustre-MDT0003/identity_upcall=NONE: wrote only 1\n\nand later in the same test\nStarting mds1:   /dev/mapper/mds1_flakey /mnt/lustre-mds1\nCMD: trevis-67vm4 mkdir -p /mnt/lustre-mds1; mount -t lustre   /dev/mapper/mds1_flakey /mnt/lustre-mds1\ntrevis-67vm4: mount.lustre: according to /etc/mtab /dev/mapper/mds1_flakey is already mounted on /mnt/lustre-mds1\nStart of /dev/mapper/mds1_flakey on mds1 failed 17\nCMD: trevis-67vm4 lctl get_param -n mdt.lustre-MDT0000.identity_upcall\n/usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh: line 4732: mdt.lustre-MDT0000.identity_upcall: command not found\nCMD: trevis-67vm4 lctl set_param -n mdt.lustre-MDT0000.identity_upcall \"NONE\"\ntrevis-67vm4: error: set_param: setting /sys/fs/lustre/mdt/lustre-MDT0000/identity_upcall=NONE: wrote only 1\n\nAre these errors expected?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
